      <section eId="sec_CCP-2674">
        <num>CCP 2674</num>
        <heading>2674. Â Attorney appointed to represent unrepresented defendant</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2674__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the defendant is an absentee;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2674__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the debtor is dead, no succession representative has been appointed, and his heirs and legatees have not been sent into possession;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2674__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the debtor's property is under the administration of a legal representative, but the latter has died, resigned, or been removed from office, and no successor thereof has qualified;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2674__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the defendant is a corporation or a partnership upon which process cannot be served for any reason; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-2674__subsec_5">
          <num>(5)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When the defendant is a minor, or a mental incompetent, who has no legal representative at the time of the institution of the proceeding.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111505</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
